panese baths in San Francisco—and a little bit about Chaucer too. Ultimately, Huerta sketches out habits of living while thinking that allow us to consider what it means to live with and try to peer beyond history even as we are caught up in the middle of it.Duke University Press Scholars of Color First Book Award recipient  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCultural pluralismzIllinoiszChicago. 0aDecolonizationxStudy and teaching (Higher). 0aEthnic restaurantszIllinoiszChicago. 0aEthnicity. 0aFeminist criticism. 0aFood habitsxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aMexican American cookingxSocial aspects. 0aMexican AmericansxEthnic identity. 0aMexican AmericanszIllinoiszChicagovBiography. 0aMexican AmericanszIllinoiszChicago. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Cultural, Ethnic & Regional / Hispanic & Latino.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478021483?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478021483423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478021483/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075417-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  a